  "text": "Below, we will make use of a number of facts about Fourier transforms of perverse sheaves on g that are originally due to Lusztig [L2] and were later revisited by Mirković [Mi] . The latter is a more suitable reference for us, because it is relatively straightforward to see that Mirković's arguments are independent of the coefficient field F. Proof. The first assertion is immediate from the definition. According to [CITATION_1] Lemma 4 .2], Fourier-Sato transform commutes with restriction and induction, so the second assertion above follows using (3.1) and Lemma 3.4. F) is an autoequivalence, and R is its inverse.",
